properties.USER_Name: William Osler Health System - Peel Memorial
properties.USER_Notes: Location: Peel Memorial Centre for Integrated Health and Wellness, 20 Lynch Street in Brampton. This space is located in a self-contained area at Peel Memorial and does not impact other patients who are attending the Urgent Care Centre or outpatient services at the site. Osler continues to be a safe place to receive care. Entrance: Separate outside entrance on the South side of the building, as well as dedicated outdoor parking next to the entrance. On-site directions will be available.

properties.USER_Notes:
You should come to the Assessment Centre, not the Emergency Department, if:

    You have a new or worsening cough and/or fever, and
    In the past 14 days have either travelled outside of Canada or been in contact with someone who has been diagnosed with COVID-19.

Patients who meet the criteria above will be tested for COVID-19, which involves taking a sample from the throat or nose with a swab.

properties.USER_Notes: Mackenzie Health will be activating an assessment centre on the evening of Monday, March 16. Assessments will be done by appointment. The intake process will be confirmed on Monday. The assessment centre will be located at our Medical Urgent Care Clinic (MUCC) which has a separate entrance and is close enough to the emergency department in case someone being assessed requires urgent care. We’re committed to being part of the important work that’s being done across the province to find solutions to contain the spread of COVID-19.
